Peru Stocks: Atacocha, Buenaventura, Maple, Pomalca, Telefonica

-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 
2011-05-31T21:59:45Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-31/peru-stocks-atacocha-buenaventura-maple-pomalca-telefonica.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and share prices are as of 4:10 p.m.  New York  time.  The Lima General Index rebounded 1.6 percent to 21,566.07,
after losing 5.2 percent yesterday. The MSCI All Peru Capped
Index fell for a third day, declining 1.2 percent to 2,780.31.  Industrial stocks and utilities gained as investors
speculated that yesterday’s selloff was overdone, said Arlen Lahura, a trader at Lima-based brokerage Coril SAB.  Maple Energy Plc. (MPLE)  , the oil and natural gas
producer with operations in Peru, jumped 8.9 percent to 98 cents
after crude rose in New York.  Casa Grande  (CASAGRC1 PE), Peru’s
largest sugar producer and a unit of Gloria SA, rose 7.9 percent
to 16.40 soles after sugar advanced in New York. Telefonica del
Peru SAA (TEF PE), the local unit of  Telefonica SA (TEF) , gained 6.3
percent to $24.99. Empresa Agroindustrial Pomalca SA (POMALCC1
PE), a unit of Grupo Oviedo, rose 5.9 percent to 54 centimos.  Miners gained after silver and lead rose in New York and
 London .  Cia. Minera Atacocha SA (ATACOBC1 PE), the Lima-based
silver and lead producer, advanced 4.5 percent to 1.16 soles.
Cia. de Minas Buenaventura SAA (BVN PE), the country’s biggest
precious-metals miner, climbed 4.3 percent to $43.80. Volcan Cia
Minera SAA (VOLCABC1 PE), Peru’s largest silver producer, rose
1.9 percent to 3.23 soles.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  